THe following Relation, I am going to make, is a Subject of ſuch Marvellous and Supernatural Aſtoniſhment, that I dare not pretend to fathom it, by the Line and Plummet of Humane Reaſon. The Works of God are unſearchable, and paſt Man's finding out. It is beyond all contradiction, that the Infinite Being has opened the Mouth of Dumb Irrational Creatures, Birds and Beaſts, and by them check'd the incorrigiblelneſs of wicked Man; the Example of Balaam's Aſs manifeſts One; and, to go no further, our Modern Speaking Raven (a Miracle yet freſh in our Memories) confirms the other. I muſt confeſs, the enſuing Narrative, infinitely creats a much greater Admiration;
First, As its Appearance is in the likeneſs of a Dove, that once Repreſentative (if I may ſo ſay) of the Holy Ghost: And Secondly, As it was ſeated on a Rainbow, That Token of the Covenant between God and
Man, That the Waters ſhould no more become a Flood to deſtroy all Fleſh.
